<h3 id="decentralized-finance">Decentralized Finance</h3>
<p>I work in a space called decentralized finance (DeFi, if we must have a short, catchy nickname). The not so modest goal of DeFi is often stated as creating a brand new monetary system on top of public blockchains ğŸ§. If you think about our existing monetary system and some of its components, someone is trying to create a version of this in DeFi. Within the industry there are varied <a href="https://www.finivi.com/ethereum-defi-platforms/">applications</a> that focus on lending, exchanges, derivatives, prediction markets, and no loss games. As someone who comes from a traditional finance background, I came into the space as a real curmudgeon. I think about the regulatory moat that banks have surrounding their businesses coupled with a healthy dose of skepticism about the utility of blockchains. That combination is having me execute some real mental gymnastics to have an open mind about DeFi applications.</p>

